changeKernel(address).notice: Points the adapter to reference a new kernel address. This function can         only be called by the active kernel, and is used to perform migrations by         telling all policies and modules where the new kernel is located before         actually performing the migration.

clearUserRecord(address).notice: Clear a user's record after they have served their punishment or appealed successfully.

configureDependencies().notice: Upon policy activation, configures the modules that the policy depends on.         If a module is ever upgraded that this policy depends on, the kernel will         call this function again to ensure this policy has the current address         of the module.

enforcePunishment(address,uint256).notice: Enforce punishment based on similarity score.

freezePaymentEscrow().notice: Freezes the payment escrow module so that no proxy upgrades can take         place. This action is non-reversible.

freezeStorage().notice: Freezes the storage module so that no proxy upgrades can take place. This         action is non-reversible.

isUserBanned(address).notice: Check if a user is currently banned.

isUserBlacklisted(address).notice: Check if a user is currently blacklisted.

requestPermissions().notice: Upon policy activation, permissions are requested from the kernel to access         particular keycode <> function selector pairs. Once these permissions are         granted, they do not change and can only be revoked when the policy is         deactivated by the kernel.

setActiveStatus(bool).notice: Allows the kernel to grant or revoke the active status of the policy.

setFee(uint256).notice: Sets the protocol fee numerator. Numerator cannot be greater than 10,000.

setGuardEmergencyUpgrade(address).notice: Sets the guard emergency upgrade address.

setMaxConsiderationItems(uint256).notice: Sets the maximum consideration items for a single order.

setMaxOfferItems(uint256).notice: Sets the maximum offer items for a single order.

skim(address,address).notice: Skims all protocol fees from the escrow module to the target address.

toggleWhitelistAsset(address,uint8).notice: Toggles whether a token can be rented.

toggleWhitelistAssetBatch(address[],uint.notice: Toggles whether a batch of tokens can be rented.

toggleWhitelistDelegate(address,bool).notice: Toggle whether an address can be delegate called by a rental safe.

toggleWhitelistExtension(address,uint8).notice: Updates an extension with a bitmap that indicates whether the extension         can be enabled or disabled by the rental safe. A valid bitmap is any         decimal value that is less than or equal to 3 (0x11).

toggleWhitelistPayment(address,bool).notice: Toggles whether a token can be used as a payment.

toggleWhitelistPaymentBatch(address[],bo.notice: Toggles whether a batch of tokens can be used as payment.

upgradePaymentEscrow(address).notice: Upgrades the payment escrow module to a newer implementation.         The new implementation contract must adhere to ERC-1822.

upgradeStorage(address).notice: Upgrades the storage module to a newer implementation. The new         implementation contract must adhere to ERC-1822.
